OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMost-expensive Mondrian    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffetches $51m at auction    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A 1930s painting by Piet Mondrian has  
OL,6, sold for $51m (#43m) in a New York     
OL,7, auction, a record for the artist's     
OL,8, work.                                  
OL,10,FThe piece was last sold in 1983 for    
OL,11,F$2.15m, which is equivalent to $6.4m   
OL,12,F(#5.4m) in today's money.              
OL,14,FThe head of impressionist and modern   
OL,15,Fart at Sotheby's, where the painting   
OL,16,Fwas auctioned, described the purchase  
OL,17,Fas "a once in a generation occurrence".
OL,19,FAn unnamed collector from Asia bought  
OL,20,Fthe artwork on Monday.                 
